            <p><a href="images/suc_img/year3_8.jpg"><img class="right" src="images/suc_img/year3_8.jpg" /></a>It is regrettable that Gylis, our expedition leader, is likely to be on the wrong side of the walls when they go up.  I do not make this decision lightly, but I make it for all of us.  Her chances of survival are not good.</p>
			<h2>8 Granite</h2>
			<p>Hope.  The caverns have been walled off, with the beast on the other side.  I turn now to reorganization of the militia, in the hopes that we can repel the goblin threat.  Great Horned Owl Men have also been spotted on the surface.  Meanwhile, reports of the missing continue to pour in.  My heart is heavy with the knowledge that many will later be found dead, and that many may never be found at all.</p>
			<p>I have ordered the miners to cut many tombs, and the masons to cut many coffins and slabs.</p>
			<p>Postscript: I have appointed a rudimentary medical staff under Morul Okuzol.  They will be busy. I have also tasked our bookkeeper, Edem Vathsithmuthkat, with brokering and managing work orders.</p>
